@startuml akdb-document-lifecycle
title AKDB - DB-Native Architecture Document Lifecycle
state "Draft request" as Draft
state "Canonical current
(projection may be dirty)" as Canonical
state "Projection current" as Exported
state "Verified" as Verified
state "Superseded" as Superseded
state "Deleted" as Deleted
[*] --> Draft : canonical create request
Draft --> Canonical : authoritative commit
Draft --> [*] : validation failure or rollback
(no mirror write)
Canonical --> Exported : post-commit export succeeds
Canonical --> Canonical : export fails
dirty repair work retained
Exported --> Canonical : next DB-native update commits
Exported --> Verified : repeat export + tests + drift checks
Verified --> Canonical : architecture/code change commits
Canonical --> Superseded : replacement accepted
Exported --> Superseded : replacement accepted
Superseded --> Deleted : explicit cleanup
Deleted --> [*]
note right of Exported
Exported Markdown and PlantUML are projections.
They are never create/update input for this project.
end note
note right of Canonical
Canonical state is authoritative before target I/O.
A stale projection never rolls back committed knowledge.
end note
@enduml
